Dear experts;
I would appreciate your help with the following:
I get GoF fitting a binned distribution along with some uncertainties according to this datacard.
There is a rate unc. named “Top_Rate_SR4a” which has a strange behavior:
If the prefit rate (lnN) is set in the range ~[1.485,1.535] the observed GoF is unreasonably large.
For values outside this range (like for 1.48 as in the cards pointed) results are stable and reasonable as summarized here.
Do you understand why this happens?
In case one wants to reproduce the results, the commands here [*] can be followed (all materials are in a public dir).
Thank you in advance, best regards,  Antonis
[*] cd /afs/cern.ch/work/a/agapitos/public/WWW/Combine2/CMSSW_11_3_4/src/HiggsAnalysis/CombinedLimit/investigation
text2workspace.py datacard_SR4a_2000_1300.txt -o workspace_SR4a_2000_1300.root;
combine -M FitDiagnostics workspace_SR4a_2000_1300.root;
combine -M GoodnessOfFit datacard_SR4a_2000_1300.txt --algo=saturated  -D data_obs --fixedSignalStrength 0 --bypassFrequentistFit -n _SR4a_2000_1300;
combine -M GoodnessOfFit datacard_SR4a_2000_1300.txt --algo=saturated --toysFreq   --fixedSignalStrength 0 --bypassFrequentistFit -n _SR4a_2000_1300Toy -t 500;
python plot_GoF.py --ObsFile higgsCombine_SR4a_2000_1300.GoodnessOfFit.mH120.root --ToyFile higgsCombine_SR4a_2000_1300Toy.GoodnessOfFit.mH120.123456.root --figName GoF_SR4a_2000_1300;

Dear Andrew;
Thank you very much for the response and the study, I appreciated it a lot. I might come back with more questions if needed.
Best regards, Antonis
